      "content": "that makes sense. but when you say the evidence is mixed, aren't the statistics usually more concrete? like, if studies show a correlation between laws and lower crime, isn't that a more \"factual\" argument than just debating what the constitution means? help me understand why one wouldn't just be seen as more valid than the other.",
